cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use readme2demo in your work, please cite it as below."
title: "readme2demo: verified tutorials and demo videos from a repo's README"
abstract: >-
  readme2demo points an AI agent at a repository, runs its README inside a
  hardened Docker sandbox, independently replays the distilled result in a
  fresh container, and only then publishes a tutorial, a step-by-step guide, a
  troubleshooting doc, structured HowTo JSON-LD, and a demo video that executes
  every step on camera. The core guarantee: nothing is published that a
  clean-room replay did not execute.
type: software
authors:
  - name: "readme2demo contributors"
    alias: alphacrack
repository-code: "https://github.com/alphacrack/readme2demo"
url: "https://github.com/alphacrack/readme2demo"
license: MIT
version: 0.1.0
date-released: "2026-07-05"
keywords:
  - ai-agents
  - developer-tools
  - documentation
  - docs-as-code
  - tutorial-generator
  - demo-video
  - sandbox
  - verification
  - llm
